observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the City Mayor instruct the City Treasurer and Market Supervisor to:
a. issue the new Contracts of Lease and/or facilitate the execution of formal agreements with the market stallholders, making sure that the said contracts are prepared in accordance with the 2015 Market Code of General Trias;
b. send demand letters to delinquent stallholders to collect the market stall rental fees and electricity bills totaling P4,881,882.66 plus the corresponding surcharges, with the reminder that their failure to settle their accounts within 30 days from due date is a sufficient ground for the automatic cancellation of the contract of lease;
c. require all market stallholders to secure Mayor’s or business permits and license, otherwise, impose upon them the sanctions or penalties provided under relevant City ordinance/s;
d. investigate and explain the discrepancies between the City Treasurer’s Office (CTO) and Business Permits and Licensing Office (BPLO) records, specifically on the 39 stallholders who secured business permits from the BPLO but whose names did not appear in the record of the CTO as stall lessees; and on stall number 147 which appeared to be vacant per CTO’s records, but a business permit was shown to have been issued to a lessee by the BPLO;
e. investigate and explain why seven business owners with permits were allowed to lease two or more market stalls which were not located in the same section of the market, in violation of Section 16 of the 2015 Market Code of General Trias;
f. update and complete the records of individual market stallholders to include relevant information such as their names, residential addresses, contact numbers, business permits and license numbers and issuance dates, market rental fees and/or electricity bills due from them, amount paid and outstanding balance/s, if there is/are any, and other data that would facilitate the proper monitoring of their compliance with the 2015 Market Code; and
g. submit the list or records of delinquent stallholders accounts to the City Accounting Office for proper recording in the books of accounts of the City; and
h. henceforth, ensure that the provisions of the 2015 Market Code of General Trias, particularly those related to the collection of market fees, imposition of surcharges for late or non-payment of fees, cancellation of the contracts of lease of stalls, sub-leasing or selling of privilege for occupancy of stalls, leasing of two or more stalls to one person and securing of business permit and license are strictly enforced, and that collections and receivables from market stallholders are properly accounted in the books of the City.

We recommended that the City Mayor direct the:
a) Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) Secretariat to submit the necessary supporting documents to the contract, together with a detailed breakdown of the Approved Budget for the Contract (ABC) and the contract amount showing in sufficient detail as derivation including the number of paleros/laborers’ crew, prices of spare parts, machine shop cost and other maintenance parts used in detailed breakdown of the contract amount;
b) City Environment and Natural Resources Officer to take steps to improve the monitoring system on the Contractor’s performance and compliance with the terms and obligations stipulated in the contract;
c) City Accountant to submit the lacking documents necessary to support the relevant disbursements made, and henceforth, refrain from processing claims with incomplete supporting documents, to avoid audit suspensions/disallowances thereon; and
d) City Budget Officer and the City Accountant to properly account the expenses for the collection, hauling and disposal of solid waste to Environment/Sanitary Services account to reflect in the Statement of Financial Performance the correct expenses incurred in the ensuing year.
